com.paypal.selion.platform.mobile.ios

Enum GestureOptions

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<GestureOptions>
      • com.paypal.selion.platform.mobile.ios.GestureOptions
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<GestureOptions>

    public enum GestureOptions
extends Enum<GestureOptions>
    GestureOptions enum houses the gesture specifications for mobile web drivers. Contains most of the gestures as stated in https://developer.apple.com/library/prerelease/ios/documentation/DeveloperTools/Reference/UIAutomationRef/index.html

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      static class  GestureOptions.TapOffset
      The TapOffset acts as a utility class for converting cartesion coordinates (x, y) to JSON representation.
      static class  GestureOptions.TapOptions
      The TapOption class serves as a utility class to convert value based GestureOptions to JSON objects.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • TAP_COUNT

        public static final GestureOptions TAP_COUNT
        Tap count. The number of taps that compose the specified gesture. The default value is 1 (single tap).

      • TOUCH_COUNT

        public static final GestureOptions TOUCH_COUNT
        Touch count. The number of touches to use in the specified gesture. (Effectively, the number of fingers a user would use to make the specified gesture.) The default touch count value is 1.

      • START_OFFSET

        public static final GestureOptions START_OFFSET
        Start offset. The offset to use for the specified tap gesture. The default offset value is {x:0.0, y:0.0}. See the discussion for details.

      • END_OFFSET

        public static final GestureOptions END_OFFSET
        End offset. The last offset to use for a multiple-point gesture. The default value is {x:0.0, y:0.0}. See the discussion for details.

      • CENTER_OFFSET

        public static final GestureOptions CENTER_OFFSET
        Center offset. The offset to use for the center of the rotate gesture. The default offset value is {x:0.0, y:0.0}.

      • TAP_OFFSET

        public static final GestureOptions TAP_OFFSET
        Tap offset. The offset to use for the specified tap gesture. The default offset value is {x:0.0, y:0.0}. See the discussion for details.

      • RADIUS

        public static final GestureOptions RADIUS
        Radius. The distance in points from the center to the edge of the circular path.

      • ROTATION

        public static final GestureOptions ROTATION
        Rotation. The length of rotation in radians. The default is pi (Ï€).

      • DURATION

        public static final GestureOptions DURATION
        Duration. The length of hold time for the specified gesture. The default duration value for a tap is 0. The default value for touch-and-hold gestures (such as drag, pinch open, and pinch close) is 1.

      • X

        public static final GestureOptions X
        X coordinate, or offset in the range 0 to 1 inclusive

      • Y

        public static final GestureOptions Y
        Y coordinate, or offset in the range 0 to 1 inclusive
